Write the constructor method in the Shell class.
Remember to respond with a snippet in the form of the following:
```
class Shell {
    constructor(faces) {
        // your code here
    }
}
```

```javascript
class Shell {
    constructor(faces) {
        if (!faces || !Array.isArray(faces) || faces.length === 0) {
            throw new Error('Shell must have at least one face.');
        }
        this.faces = faces;
    }
}
```
